It&#x27;s worth noting that in Perl the &#x27;or&#x27; and &#x27;and&#x27; operators are not equivalent to || and &&. For instance, they have super low operator precedence:<p><pre><code>  my $variable = 0 or 1;
</code></pre>
Would result in $variable == 0 because it really looks like this:<p><pre><code>  (my $variable = 0) or 1;
</code></pre>
I allowed myself to get burned by this once because I didn&#x27;t read the fine print. ^^;;
